article.description: Chassidy Fussell scored 14 of her 22 points in the first half and Texas rolled to a 79-40 victory over Arkansas-Pine Bluff Wednesday.
article.headline: Chassidy Fussell boosts No. 24 Texas in rout of Arkansas-Pine Bluff
article.linkText: Fussell boosts No. 24 Texas in rout of Pine Bluff
article.story:
AUSTIN, Texas --  Chassidy Fussell scored 14 of her 22 points in the first half and No. 24 Texas rolled to a 79-40 victory over Arkansas-Pine Bluff Wednesday.

Fussell was 8 of 12 shooting and had three 3-pointers. Yvonne Anderson scored 14 and Cokie Reed and Ashleigh Fontenette each had 10 for Texas (7-2).

Chigozianyi Okwumabua led Arkansas-Pine Bluff (0-8) with 10 points. The Golden Lions were playing their second ranked opponent in four days after losing at Kentucky (No. 7 ESPN/USA Today, No. 8 AP) on Dec. 11.

Kayla Brewer debuted for Texas on Wednesday. The transfer from South Carolina scored five points in 15 minutes.

Arkansas-Pine Bluff connected on 6 of 29 shots in the first half and Texas led 41-17 at intermission.
